Be aware that Flask, Django and RoR are back-end web development frameworks that still require a web server to start (eg. Apache) and in that way a bit more capable to fit different web server frameworks, while many web development frameworks in JS are build on top of nodejs. One clear example is express: it is in fact a web dev framework for node: you cannot use it without it.

